#: ../../I/interesting.rst:5
msgid "interesting"
msgstr "interesting"

#: ../../I/interesting.rst:7
msgid "adj\\."
msgstr "形容詞"

#: ../../I/interesting.rst:9
msgid ""
"In hacker parlance, this word has strong connotations of ‘annoying’, or "
"‘difficult’, or both. Hackers relish a challenge, and enjoy wringing all the"
" irony possible out of the ancient Chinese curse \"May you live in "
"interesting times\". Oppose :ref:`trivial`\\, :ref:`uninteresting`\\."
msgstr ""
"ハッカーの言葉遣いでは、この語は‘煩わしい’、‘難しい’、あるいはその両方という強い含みを持つ。ハッカーは挑戦を好み、古代中国の呪い「May you "
"live in interesting times(おまえが面白い時代に生きますように)」から引き出せる限りの皮肉を味わうのを楽しむ。\\ "
":ref:`trivial`\\ 、\\ :ref:`uninteresting`\\ の対義語。"
